column2: ASUW EligibilityOnly members of the Associated Students of the University of Washington (ASUW)-Seattle are able to vote in the elections.Per the ASUW Constitution,Article IV: Membership,the privileges of membership in the ASUW are: "Only members of the ASUW are entitled to vote in any ASUW election,to represent the ASUW,or to hold any office controlled by the ASUW." There are no costs to declaring membership in the ASUW. For more information about the ASUW,your student government,visit https://asuw.org.Below,you will be asked to state your intention to be a member of the ASUW in order to cast a vote. Choosing "no" means you will not be able to vote in the ASUW Elections.

column7: Candidates  Vote for your candidates below. Information about candidates is available by clicking on the respective links (links will open in a separate browser window).  For each of the eight candidate positions,you may rank your choices. For example,next to each candidate's name,rank them in order of preference,with a rank of 1 being most preferred,and so on. You may choose to rank as many or as few candidates as you wish. You may also choose to not vote for any of the candidates and ballot referenda/initiatives,and move on to the next question.  You can only rank one write-in candidate for each position.  Referenda,Initiative,and Survey questions require simple yes/no responses.You will have an opportunity to review and change your selections. Once you click VOTE you will not be able to change your selections.

column40: THANK YOU FOR YOUR RESPONSES!  Elections announcements for the 2023 ASUW Elections will be Thursday,April 20,2023,approximately 5 pm,location HUB Front Porch.  If you wish to file a complaint about the ASUW Elections process,you must file your complaint in writing,in person,with Rene Singleton,the Associate Director of Student Activities,by 5 pm Monday,April 24,2023,in Room 232 of the HUB.  Election complaint hearings will be 3 pm Wednesday,April 26,2023,in HUB 145.   For more information about ASUW Elections,please visit https://vote.asuw.org,or contact the Elections Administration Committee Co-Chairs Emily Glenn at asuwvote@uw.edu,and Bob Goldsmith at asuweac@uw.edu.
